JOHANNESBURG - Thirty local celebrities and moms have decided to help stop hunger during World Hunger Month. They met up in Soweto to feed 3,000 people. They’re urging other South Africans to also play their part. World Hunger Month highlights the importance of good nutrition. Experts agree that tackling malnutrition strengthens the immune system and also improves infant, child and maternal health. That’s why it made sense for these moms to serve samp, beans, beef and chicken stew. By the end of the day, the goal was achieved -- 3,000 mouths fed. * Watch the full video report by Lindiwe Sithole in the gallery above. eNCA